This paper is about extracting relational triples from unstructured text, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR). The proposed framework is based on a principled problem formulation and uses a novel approach to handle overlapping triples. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and neural networks (cs.NE).
